            "title": "Carney expects U.S. to respect Canadian sovereignty amid Albertan separatist push",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney has said he expects the U.S. government to respect Canadian sovereignty, after Albertan separatists reportedly met with Trump administration officials to seek support for their breakaway movement.</p>\n<p>Leaders of the Alberta Prosperity Project met U.S. State Department officials in Washington three times since April last year, the <em>Financial Times </em>reported, citing people familiar with the talks. The APP wants the oil-rich province to be independent from Canada.</p>\n<p>The group also <a href=\"https://www.ft.com/content/11dc2140-6a5d-4536-b766-52c920affcc7\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"sought\">sought</a> another meeting with U.S. officials next month to request a $500B credit facility to help bankroll the province if the separatists win a referendum on independence. No such referendum is planned yet.</p>\n<p>\"I expect the U.S. administration to respect Canadian sovereignty. I'm always clear in my conversations with President Trump to that effect,\" Carney said, when asked about the APP meetings, adding that Trump never raised the separatism issue with him.</p>\n<p>A White House official said the administration meets with several civil society groups, asserting that \"no support or commitments were conveyed.\"</p>\n<p>\"To go to a foreign country and to ask for assistance in breaking up Canada, there's an old-fashioned word for that, and that word is treason,\" said David Eby, premier of British Columbia, which borders Alberta to the east.</p>\n<p>Alberta Premier Danielle Smith said while she supports \"a strong and sovereign Alberta within a united Canada,\" she wouldn't \"demonize\" the separatists.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
